  "description": "The immediate sequel to <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Heisei+Shima+Zenpen\"> Heisei Shin OniOni Shima: Zenpen</a>, released simultaneously with the first part. The two games are based on the popular Japanese fairy tale about the &quot;peach boy&quot; Momotaro. He was found by an old man inside a huge peach, and when he grew up, he swore to slay the evil demons and to take their treasure. On his way to the demon land he met three animals: a dog, a monkey, and a pheasant, who helped him on his quest. The second game is split into two parts: the first tells the story of the pheasant Ohana and the princess Otohime, while the second tells about the ultimate battle of the heroes against the evil.<br><br>The game is an adventure in which you interact with the environments by selecting commands from a menu. As a pheasant, you can also fly from location to location. There are several times sequences when you must act quickly in order to make the game progress.",
